Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.ClinicalUseDefinition` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-ClinicalUseDefinition Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-10 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionClinicalUseDefinition

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element ClinicalUseDefinition for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Basic

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • Use this Extension: Cross-version Profile for R5.ClinicalUseDefinition for use in FHIR R4

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element ClinicalUseDefinition for use in FHIR R4.

  • type: code: indication | contraindication | interaction | undesirable-effect | warning.
  • category: CodeableConcept: A categorisation of the issue, primarily for dividing warnings into subject heading areas such as "Pregnancy and Lactation", "Overdose", "Effects on Ability to Drive and Use Machines".
  • status: CodeableConcept: Whether this is a current issue or one that has been retired etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element ClinicalUseDefinition for use in FHIR R4.

  • type: code: indication | contraindication | interaction | undesirable-effect | warning.
  • category: CodeableConcept: A categorisation of the issue, primarily for dividing warnings into subject heading areas such as "Pregnancy and Lactation", "Overdose", "Effects on Ability to Drive and Use Machines".
  • status: CodeableConcept: Whether this is a current issue or one that has been retired etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
